[12:16:03    12]  
[12:16:03    12]  ## Next target
[12:16:03    12]  
[12:16:03    12] -- Migrate linked `cJSON` node ownership/allocation (`cJSON_New_Item`, `cJSON_Delete`, and related fields) to safe ownership. That prerequisite will allow the parser entry logic to become a safe slice-based implementation helper.
[12:16:03    12] +- Migrate linked `cJSON` node ownership/allocation (`cJSON_New_Item`, `cJSON_Delete`, and related fields) to safe ownership. This is cross-cutting: first map all tree mutation, reference-node, duplication, and FFI-pointer return paths before changing the node representation.
[12:16:03    12] +- Prefer a small prerequisite that directly moves one node field or allocation path to safe ownership if the full link migration cannot be completed in one iteration.
[12:16:03    12]  
[12:16:03    12]  ## Pitfalls
[12:16:03    12]  
[12:16:03    12]  - Preserve whitespace-at-end rewind and the original `offset + 4 < length` BOM condition.
[12:16:03    12]  - Do not copy parse input: returned parse/error pointers must point into the caller buffer.
[12:16:03    12]  - Keep exported `*_ffi` signatures unchanged. Do not create a new unsafe implementation helper merely to preserve the old façade structure.
[12:16:03    12] +- `cJSON` hook allocators are public behavior; do not silently replace custom-hook allocation/deallocation with `Box` unless the hook behavior is preserved.
