[12:17:06    20]  - [done] Removed the non-exported raw parser façades (`cJSON_ParseWithOpts`, `cJSON_ParseWithLengthOpts`, `cJSON_Parse`, and `cJSON_ParseWithLength`). Their ABI work now lives only in the matching exported `*_ffi` entry points.
[12:17:06    20]  - [done] Verified `cargo check-unsafe2 --manifest-path rust/Cargo.toml` and `bash ./test_translated.sh` (18/18 tests passed).
[12:17:06    20]  - [done] Replaced the non-exported `cJSON_Version` implementation's mutable static and C `sprintf` call with an immutable Rust byte-string helper. The exported `cJSON_Version_ffi` ABI is unchanged.
[12:17:06    20] +- [done] Replaced the non-exported cJSON type/value query functions with safe `&cJSON`/`Option<&cJSON>` helpers; the exported ABI wrappers now perform the raw-pointer conversion.
[12:17:06    20]  
[12:17:06    20]  ## Next target
[12:17:06    20]  
[12:17:06    20]  - Migrate linked `cJSON` node ownership/allocation (`cJSON_New_Item`, `cJSON_Delete`, and related fields) to safe ownership. This is cross-cutting: first map all tree mutation, reference-node, duplication, and FFI-pointer return paths before changing the node representation.
[12:17:06    20] -- Prefer a small prerequisite that directly moves one node field or allocation path to safe ownership if the full link migration cannot be completed in one iteration.
[12:17:06    20] +- The safe type-query layer is now available for that migration; next, choose a small ownership prerequisite that preserves custom hook allocation/deallocation behavior.
