[12:17:15    29] +- [done] Replaced the non-exported cJSON type/value query functions with safe `&cJSON`/`Option<&cJSON>` helpers; the exported ABI wrappers now perform the raw-pointer conversion. Verified `cargo check-unsafe2` and `test_translated.sh` (18/18).
[12:17:15    29]  
[12:17:15    29]  ## Next target
[12:17:15    29]  
[12:17:15    29]  - Migrate linked `cJSON` node ownership/allocation (`cJSON_New_Item`, `cJSON_Delete`, and related fields) to safe ownership. This is cross-cutting: first map all tree mutation, reference-node, duplication, and FFI-pointer return paths before changing the node representation.
[12:17:15    29] -- Prefer a small prerequisite that directly moves one node field or allocation path to safe ownership if the full link migration cannot be completed in one iteration.
[12:17:15    29] +- The safe type-query layer is now available for that migration; next, choose a small ownership prerequisite that preserves custom hook allocation/deallocation behavior.
[12:17:15    29]  
[12:17:15    29]  ## Pitfalls
[12:17:15    29]  
[12:17:15    29] @@ -20,3 +21,4 @@
[12:17:15    29]  - Do not copy parse input: returned parse/error pointers must point into the caller buffer.
[12:17:15    29]  - Keep exported `*_ffi` signatures unchanged. Do not create a new unsafe implementation helper merely to preserve the old façade structure.
[12:17:15    29]  - `cJSON` hook allocators are public behavior; do not silently replace custom-hook allocation/deallocation with `Box` unless the hook behavior is preserved.
[12:17:15    29] +- The cJSON predicate wrappers must retain null input behavior (`false_0`); use the safe predicate helpers rather than reintroducing raw-pointer implementations.
