[12:18:31    23] codex
[12:18:31    23] The unsafe checker caught a useful constraint: moving both C-string conversions into the lookup loop increased that implementation’s unsafe operations. I’ll make both the case-sensitive and case-insensitive comparisons use the same safe byte-slice helper, so the lookup performs exactly two FFI conversions (one query key and one candidate key) instead of also calling C `strcmp`.
