[12:20:51    48] -## Next target
[12:20:51    48] +## Current target
[12:20:51    48] +
[12:20:51    48] +- Convert `cJSON_Minify` and its three pointer-walking helpers to a safe
[12:20:51    48] +  slice-based implementation. The only raw-pointer conversion will stay in
[12:20:51    48] +  the exported `cJSON_Minify_ffi` wrapper.
[12:20:51    48] +
[12:20:51    48] +## Plan
[12:20:51    48]  
[12:20:51    48] +- [in progress] Replace comment/string scanners with indexed operations on a
[12:20:51    48] +  NUL-terminated `&mut [u8]`, preserving the legacy treatment of a bare `/`
[12:20:51    48] +  (it is discarded) and unterminated comments/strings.
[12:20:51    48] +- [pending] Have `cJSON_Minify_ffi` borrow the caller's C string as a bounded
[12:20:51    48] +  mutable byte slice and dispatch to the safe helper.
[12:20:51    48] +- [pending] Run `cargo check-unsafe2` and `test_translated.sh`.
[12:20:51    48] +
[12:20:51    48] +## Deferred target
[12:20:51    48] +
[12:20:51    48]  - Migrate linked `cJSON` node ownership/allocation (`cJSON_New_Item`,
[12:20:51    48] -  `cJSON_Delete`, and related fields) to safe ownership. This is cross-cutting:
[12:20:51    48] -  first map all tree mutation, reference-node, duplication, and FFI-pointer
[12:20:51    48] -  return paths before changing the node representation.
[12:20:51    48] +  `cJSON_Delete`, and related fields) to safe ownership. Mapping showed this
[12:20:51    48] +  touches parsing, mutation, references, duplication, constructors, and every
[12:20:51    48] +  FFI node pointer, so it needs to be split into smaller ownership steps.
